### Description

Get script task context information, including script type, script content, script parameters and execution error logs, for AI analysis.

### Request Parameters

#### Query Parameters

| Field                      | Type   | Required | Description                                                                                                              |
|----------------------------|--------|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| bk_scope_type              | string | Yes      | Resource scope type. Allowed values: biz - Business, biz_set - Business Set                                              |
| bk_scope_id                | string | Yes      | Resource scope ID, corresponding to bk_scope_type. Indicates Biz ID or Biz Set ID                                        |
| job_instance_id            | long   | Yes      | Job instance ID                                                                                                          |
| step_instance_id           | long   | Yes      | Step instance ID                                                                                                         |
| execute_count              | int    | Yes      | Execution count (retry count, 0 for first execution)                                                                    |
| batch                      | int    | No       | Rolling execution batch number. Not required for non-rolling steps                                                       |
| execute_object_type        | int    | Yes      | Execute object type. 1 - Host, 2 - Container                                                                            |
| execute_object_resource_id | long   | Yes      | Execute object resource ID (e.g. bk_host_id for hosts)                                                                  |
| content                    | string | No       | User-selected error log content. If not empty, returned as-is as error log; if empty, the task log will be auto-fetched |

### Request Example

- GET

```json
/api/v4/get_script_task_context?bk_scope_type=biz&bk_scope_id=1&job_instance_id=100&step_instance_id=200&execute_count=0&execute_object_type=1&execute_object_resource_id=101
```

